  {
    "author": "Richard Barnes",
    "text": "<p>In other words, there's a pretty exact analogy between VC-without-KB and <code>\"alg\": \"none\"</code>.  Here's a thing that is syntactically similar to a thing that provides a security property, <strong>but does not actually provide that property</strong>.  You will get exactly the same bugs and vulnerabilities as with <code>\"alg\": \"none\"</code>.</p>",
